 2196      pub fn resolve_single_import(@mut self,
 2197                                   module_: @mut Module,
 2198                                   containing_module: @mut Module,
 2199                                   target: ident,
 2200                                   source: ident,
 2201                                   directive: &ImportDirective)
 2202                                   -> ResolveResult<()> {
 2203          debug!("(resolving single import) resolving `%s` = `%s::%s` from \
 2204                  `%s`",
 2205                 self.session.str_of(target),
 2206                 self.module_to_str(containing_module),
 2207                 self.session.str_of(source),
 2208                 self.module_to_str(module_));
 2209  
 2210          // We need to resolve both namespaces for this to succeed.
 2211          //
 2212          // FIXME #4949: See if there's some way of handling namespaces in
 2213          // a more generic way. We have two of them; it seems worth
 2214          // doing...
 2215  
 2216          let mut value_result = UnknownResult;
 2217          let mut type_result = UnknownResult;
 2218  
 2219          // Search for direct children of the containing module.
 2220          match containing_module.children.find(&source) {
 2221              None => {
 2222                  // Continue.
 2223              }
 2224              Some(child_name_bindings) => {
 2225                  if child_name_bindings.defined_in_namespace(ValueNS) {
 2226                      value_result = BoundResult(containing_module,
 2227                                                 *child_name_bindings);
 2228                  }
 2229                  if child_name_bindings.defined_in_namespace(TypeNS) {
 2230                      type_result = BoundResult(containing_module,
 2231                                                *child_name_bindings);
 2232                  }
 2233              }
 2234          }
 2235  
 2236          // Unless we managed to find a result in both namespaces (unlikely),
 2237          // search imports as well.
 2238          match (value_result, type_result) {
 2239              (BoundResult(*), BoundResult(*)) => {} // Continue.
 2240              _ => {
 2241                  // If there is an unresolved glob at this point in the
 2242                  // containing module, bail out. We don't know enough to be
 2243                  // able to resolve this import.
 2244  
 2245                  if containing_module.glob_count > 0 {
 2246                      debug!("(resolving single import) unresolved glob; \
 2247                              bailing out");
 2248                      return Indeterminate;
 2249                  }
 2250  
 2251                  // Now search the exported imports within the containing
 2252                  // module.
 2253  
 2254                  match containing_module.import_resolutions.find(&source) {
 2255                      None => {
 2256                          // The containing module definitely doesn't have an
 2257                          // exported import with the name in question. We can
 2258                          // therefore accurately report that the names are
 2259                          // unbound.
 2260  
 2261                          if value_result.is_unknown() {
 2262                              value_result = UnboundResult;
 2263                          }
 2264                          if type_result.is_unknown() {
 2265                              type_result = UnboundResult;
 2266                          }
 2267                      }
 2268                      Some(import_resolution)
 2269                              if import_resolution.outstanding_references
 2270                                  == 0 => {
 2271  
 2272                          fn get_binding(this: @mut Resolver,
 2273                                         import_resolution:
 2274                                            @mut ImportResolution,
 2275                                         namespace: Namespace)
 2276                                      -> NamespaceResult {
 2277  
 2278                              // Import resolutions must be declared with "pub"
 2279                              // in order to be exported.
 2280                              if import_resolution.privacy == Private {
 2281                                  return UnboundResult;
 2282                              }
 2283  
 2284                              match (*import_resolution).
 2285                                      target_for_namespace(namespace) {
 2286                                  None => {
 2287                                      return UnboundResult;
 2288                                  }
 2289                                  Some(target) => {
 2290                                      let id = import_resolution.id(namespace);
 2291                                      this.used_imports.insert(id);
 2292                                      return BoundResult(target.target_module,
 2293                                                         target.bindings);
 2294                                  }
 2295                              }
 2296                          }
 2297  
 2298                          // The name is an import which has been fully
 2299                          // resolved. We can, therefore, just follow it.
 2300                          if value_result.is_unknown() {
 2301                              value_result = get_binding(self, *import_resolution,
 2302                                                         ValueNS);
 2303                          }
 2304                          if type_result.is_unknown() {
 2305                              type_result = get_binding(self, *import_resolution,
 2306                                                        TypeNS);
 2307                          }
 2308                      }
 2309                      Some(_) => {
 2310                          // The import is unresolved. Bail out.
 2311                          debug!("(resolving single import) unresolved import; \
 2312                                  bailing out");
 2313                          return Indeterminate;
 2314                      }
 2315                  }
 2316              }
 2317          }
 2318  
 2319          // If we didn't find a result in the type namespace, search the
 2320          // external modules.
 2321          match type_result {
 2322              BoundResult(*) => {}
 2323              _ => {
 2324                  match containing_module.external_module_children
 2325                                         .find(&source) {
 2326                      None => {} // Continue.
 2327                      Some(module) => {
 2328                          let name_bindings =
 2329                              @mut Resolver::create_name_bindings_from_module(
 2330                                  *module);
 2331                          type_result = BoundResult(containing_module,
 2332                                                    name_bindings);
 2333                      }
 2334                  }
 2335              }
 2336          }
 2337  
 2338          // We've successfully resolved the import. Write the results in.
 2339          assert!(module_.import_resolutions.contains_key(&target));
 2340          let import_resolution = module_.import_resolutions.get(&target);
 2341  
 2342          match value_result {
 2343              BoundResult(target_module, name_bindings) => {
 2344                  debug!("(resolving single import) found value target");
 2345                  import_resolution.value_target =
 2346                      Some(Target(target_module, name_bindings));
 2347                  import_resolution.value_id = directive.id;
 2348              }
 2349              UnboundResult => { /* Continue. */ }
 2350              UnknownResult => {
 2351                  fail!("value result should be known at this point");
 2352              }
 2353          }
 2354          match type_result {
 2355              BoundResult(target_module, name_bindings) => {
 2356                  debug!("(resolving single import) found type target: %?",
 2357                          name_bindings.type_def.unwrap().type_def);
 2358                  import_resolution.type_target =
 2359                      Some(Target(target_module, name_bindings));
 2360                  import_resolution.type_id = directive.id;
 2361              }
 2362              UnboundResult => { /* Continue. */ }
 2363              UnknownResult => {
 2364                  fail!("type result should be known at this point");
 2365              }
 2366          }
 2367  
 2368          let i = import_resolution;
 2369          let mut resolve_fail = false;
 2370          let mut priv_fail = false;
 2371          match (i.value_target, i.type_target) {
 2372              // If this name wasn't found in either namespace, it's definitely
 2373              // unresolved.
 2374              (None, None) => { resolve_fail = true; }
 2375              // If it's private, it's also unresolved.
 2376              (Some(t), None) | (None, Some(t)) => {
 2377                  let bindings = &mut *t.bindings;
 2378                  match bindings.type_def {
 2379                      Some(ref type_def) => {
 2380                          if type_def.privacy == Private {
 2381                              priv_fail = true;
 2382                          }
 2383                      }
 2384                      _ => ()
 2385                  }
 2386                  match bindings.value_def {
 2387                      Some(ref value_def) => {
 2388                          if value_def.privacy == Private {
 2389                              priv_fail = true;
 2390                          }
 2391                      }
 2392                      _ => ()
 2393                  }
 2394              }
 2395              // It's also an error if there's both a type and a value with this
 2396              // name, but both are private
 2397              (Some(val), Some(ty)) => {
 2398                  match (val.bindings.value_def, ty.bindings.value_def) {
 2399                      (Some(ref value_def), Some(ref type_def)) =>
 2400                          if value_def.privacy == Private
 2401                              && type_def.privacy == Private {
 2402                                  priv_fail = true;
 2403                          },
 2404                      _ => ()
 2405                  }
 2406              }
 2407          }
 2408  
 2409          let span = directive.span;
 2410          if resolve_fail {
 2411              self.session.span_err(span, fmt!("unresolved import: there is no `%s` in `%s`",
 2412                                               self.session.str_of(source),
 2413                                               self.module_to_str(containing_module)));
 2414              return Failed;
 2415          } else if priv_fail {
 2416              self.session.span_err(span, fmt!("unresolved import: found `%s` in `%s` but it is \
 2417                                               private", self.session.str_of(source),
 2418                                               self.module_to_str(containing_module)));
 2419              return Failed;
 2420          }
 2421  
 2422          assert!(import_resolution.outstanding_references >= 1);
 2423          import_resolution.outstanding_references -= 1;
 2424  
 2425          debug!("(resolving single import) successfully resolved import");
 2426          return Success(());
 2427      }
 2428  
 2429      // Resolves a glob import. Note that this function cannot fail; it either
 2430      // succeeds or bails out (as importing * from an empty module or a module
 2431      // that exports nothing is valid).
 2432      pub fn resolve_glob_import(@mut self,
 2433                                 privacy: Privacy,
 2434                                 module_: @mut Module,
 2435                                 containing_module: @mut Module,
 2436                                 id: NodeId)
 2437                                 -> ResolveResult<()> {
 2438          // This function works in a highly imperative manner; it eagerly adds
 2439          // everything it can to the list of import resolutions of the module
 2440          // node.
 2441          debug!("(resolving glob import) resolving %? glob import", privacy);
 2442  
 2443          // We must bail out if the node has unresolved imports of any kind
 2444          // (including globs).
 2445          if !(*containing_module).all_imports_resolved() {
 2446              debug!("(resolving glob import) target module has unresolved \
 2447                      imports; bailing out");
 2448              return Indeterminate;
 2449          }
 2450  
 2451          assert_eq!(containing_module.glob_count, 0);
 2452  
 2453          // Add all resolved imports from the containing module.
 2454          for (ident, target_import_resolution) in containing_module.import_resolutions.iter() {
 2455  
 2456              debug!("(resolving glob import) writing module resolution \
 2457                      %? into `%s`",
 2458                     target_import_resolution.type_target.is_none(),
 2459                     self.module_to_str(module_));
 2460  
 2461              // Here we merge two import resolutions.
 2462              match module_.import_resolutions.find(ident) {
 2463                  None if target_import_resolution.privacy == Public => {
 2464                      // Simple: just copy the old import resolution.
 2465                      let new_import_resolution =
 2466                          @mut ImportResolution(privacy, id);
 2467                      new_import_resolution.value_target =
 2468                          target_import_resolution.value_target;
 2469                      new_import_resolution.type_target =
 2470                          target_import_resolution.type_target;
 2471  
 2472                      module_.import_resolutions.insert
 2473                          (*ident, new_import_resolution);
 2474                  }
 2475                  None => { /* continue ... */ }
 2476                  Some(&dest_import_resolution) => {
 2477                      // Merge the two import resolutions at a finer-grained
 2478                      // level.
 2479  
 2480                      match target_import_resolution.value_target {
 2481                          None => {
 2482                              // Continue.
 2483                          }
 2484                          Some(value_target) => {
 2485                              dest_import_resolution.value_target =
 2486                                  Some(value_target);
 2487                          }
 2488                      }
 2489                      match target_import_resolution.type_target {
 2490                          None => {
 2491                              // Continue.
 2492                          }
 2493                          Some(type_target) => {
 2494                              dest_import_resolution.type_target =
 2495                                  Some(type_target);
 2496                          }
 2497                      }
 2498                  }
 2499              }
 2500          }
 2501  
 2502          let merge_import_resolution = |ident,
 2503                                         name_bindings: @mut NameBindings| {
 2504              let dest_import_resolution;
 2505              match module_.import_resolutions.find(&ident) {
 2506                  None => {
 2507                      // Create a new import resolution from this child.
 2508                      dest_import_resolution = @mut ImportResolution(privacy, id);
 2509                      module_.import_resolutions.insert
 2510                          (ident, dest_import_resolution);
 2511                  }
 2512                  Some(&existing_import_resolution) => {
 2513                      dest_import_resolution = existing_import_resolution;
 2514                  }
 2515              }
 2516  
 2517              debug!("(resolving glob import) writing resolution `%s` in `%s` \
 2518                      to `%s`, privacy=%?",
 2519                     self.session.str_of(ident),
 2520                     self.module_to_str(containing_module),
 2521                     self.module_to_str(module_),
 2522                     dest_import_resolution.privacy);
 2523  
 2524              // Merge the child item into the import resolution.
 2525              if name_bindings.defined_in_public_namespace(ValueNS) {
 2526                  debug!("(resolving glob import) ... for value target");
 2527                  dest_import_resolution.value_target =
 2528                      Some(Target(containing_module, name_bindings));
 2529              }
 2530              if name_bindings.defined_in_public_namespace(TypeNS) {
 2531                  debug!("(resolving glob import) ... for type target");
 2532                  dest_import_resolution.type_target =
 2533                      Some(Target(containing_module, name_bindings));
 2534              }
 2535          };
 2536  
 2537          // Add all children from the containing module.
 2538          for (&ident, name_bindings) in containing_module.children.iter() {
 2539              merge_import_resolution(ident, *name_bindings);
 2540          }
 2541  
 2542          // Add external module children from the containing module.
 2543          for (&ident, module) in containing_module.external_module_children.iter() {
 2544              let name_bindings =
 2545                  @mut Resolver::create_name_bindings_from_module(*module);
 2546              merge_import_resolution(ident, name_bindings);
 2547          }
 2548  
 2549          debug!("(resolving glob import) successfully resolved import");
 2550          return Success(());
 2551      }

 2553      /// Resolves the given module path from the given root `module_`.
 2554      pub fn resolve_module_path_from_root(@mut self,
 2555                                           module_: @mut Module,
 2556                                           module_path: &[ident],
 2557                                           index: uint,
 2558                                           span: span,
 2559                                           mut name_search_type: NameSearchType)
 2560                                           -> ResolveResult<@mut Module> {
 2561          let mut search_module = module_;
 2562          let mut index = index;
 2563          let module_path_len = module_path.len();
 2564  
 2565          // Resolve the module part of the path. This does not involve looking
 2566          // upward though scope chains; we simply resolve names directly in
 2567          // modules as we go.
 2568          while index < module_path_len {
 2569              let name = module_path[index];
 2570              match self.resolve_name_in_module(search_module,
 2571                                                name,
 2572                                                TypeNS,
 2573                                                name_search_type) {
 2574                  Failed => {
 2575                      let segment_name = self.session.str_of(name);
 2576                      let module_name = self.module_to_str(search_module);
 2577                      if "???" == module_name {
 2578                          let span = span {
 2579                              lo: span.lo,
 2580                              hi: span.lo + BytePos(segment_name.len()),
 2581                              expn_info: span.expn_info,
 2582                          };
 2583                          self.session.span_err(span,
 2584                                                fmt!("unresolved import. maybe \
 2585                                                      a missing `extern mod \
 2586                                                      %s`?",
 2587                                                      segment_name));
 2588                          return Failed;
 2589                      }
 2590                      self.session.span_err(span, fmt!("unresolved import: could not find `%s` in \
 2591                                                       `%s`.", segment_name, module_name));
 2592                      return Failed;
 2593                  }
 2594                  Indeterminate => {
 2595                      debug!("(resolving module path for import) module \
 2596                              resolution is indeterminate: %s",
 2597                              self.session.str_of(name));
 2598                      return Indeterminate;
 2599                  }
 2600                  Success(target) => {
 2601                      // Check to see whether there are type bindings, and, if
 2602                      // so, whether there is a module within.
 2603                      match target.bindings.type_def {
 2604                          Some(type_def) => {
 2605                              match type_def.module_def {
 2606                                  None => {
 2607                                      // Not a module.
 2608                                      self.session.span_err(span,
 2609                                                            fmt!("not a \
 2610                                                                  module `%s`",
 2611                                                                 self.session.
 2612                                                                     str_of(
 2613                                                                      name)));
 2614                                      return Failed;
 2615                                  }
 2616                                  Some(module_def) => {
 2617                                      // If we're doing the search for an
 2618                                      // import, do not allow traits and impls
 2619                                      // to be selected.
 2620                                      match (name_search_type,
 2621                                             module_def.kind) {
 2622                                          (ImportSearch, TraitModuleKind) |
 2623                                          (ImportSearch, ImplModuleKind) => {
 2624                                              self.session.span_err(
 2625                                                  span,
 2626                                                  "cannot import from a trait \
 2627                                                   or type implementation");
 2628                                              return Failed;
 2629                                          }
 2630                                          (_, _) => search_module = module_def,
 2631                                      }
 2632                                  }
 2633                              }
 2634                          }
 2635                          None => {
 2636                              // There are no type bindings at all.
 2637                              self.session.span_err(span,
 2638                                                    fmt!("not a module `%s`",
 2639                                                         self.session.str_of(
 2640                                                              name)));
 2641                              return Failed;
 2642                          }
 2643                      }
 2644                  }
 2645              }
 2646  
 2647              index += 1;
 2648  
 2649              // After the first element of the path, allow searching only
 2650              // through public identifiers.
 2651              //
 2652              // XXX: Rip this out and move it to the privacy checker.
 2653              if name_search_type == PathPublicOrPrivateSearch {
 2654                  name_search_type = PathPublicOnlySearch
 2655              }
 2656          }
 2657  
 2658          return Success(search_module);
 2659      }
 2660  
 2661      /// Attempts to resolve the module part of an import directive or path
 2662      /// rooted at the given module.
 2663      pub fn resolve_module_path(@mut self,
 2664                                 module_: @mut Module,
 2665                                 module_path: &[ident],
 2666                                 use_lexical_scope: UseLexicalScopeFlag,
 2667                                 span: span,
 2668                                 name_search_type: NameSearchType)
 2669                                 -> ResolveResult<@mut Module> {
 2670          let module_path_len = module_path.len();
 2671          assert!(module_path_len > 0);
 2672  
 2673          debug!("(resolving module path for import) processing `%s` rooted at \
 2674                 `%s`",
 2675                 self.idents_to_str(module_path),
 2676                 self.module_to_str(module_));
 2677  
 2678          // Resolve the module prefix, if any.
 2679          let module_prefix_result = self.resolve_module_prefix(module_,
 2680                                                                module_path);
 2681  
 2682          let search_module;
 2683          let start_index;
 2684          match module_prefix_result {
 2685              Failed => {
 2686                  let mpath = self.idents_to_str(module_path);
 2687                  match mpath.rfind(':') {
 2688                      Some(idx) => {
 2689                          self.session.span_err(span, fmt!("unresolved import: could not find `%s` \
 2690                                                           in `%s`",
 2691                                                           // idx +- 1 to account for the colons
 2692                                                           // on either side
 2693                                                           mpath.slice_from(idx + 1),
 2694                                                           mpath.slice_to(idx - 1)));
 2695                      },
 2696                      None => (),
 2697                  };
 2698                  return Failed;
 2699              }
 2700              Indeterminate => {
 2701                  debug!("(resolving module path for import) indeterminate; \
 2702                          bailing");
 2703                  return Indeterminate;
 2704              }
 2705              Success(NoPrefixFound) => {
 2706                  // There was no prefix, so we're considering the first element
 2707                  // of the path. How we handle this depends on whether we were
 2708                  // instructed to use lexical scope or not.
 2709                  match use_lexical_scope {
 2710                      DontUseLexicalScope => {
 2711                          // This is a crate-relative path. We will start the
 2712                          // resolution process at index zero.
 2713                          search_module = self.graph_root.get_module();
 2714                          start_index = 0;
 2715                      }
 2716                      UseLexicalScope => {
 2717                          // This is not a crate-relative path. We resolve the
 2718                          // first component of the path in the current lexical
 2719                          // scope and then proceed to resolve below that.
 2720                          let result = self.resolve_module_in_lexical_scope(
 2721                              module_,
 2722                              module_path[0]);
 2723                          match result {
 2724                              Failed => {
 2725                                  self.session.span_err(span,
 2726                                                        "unresolved name");
 2727                                  return Failed;
 2728                              }
 2729                              Indeterminate => {
 2730                                  debug!("(resolving module path for import) \
 2731                                          indeterminate; bailing");
 2732                                  return Indeterminate;
 2733                              }
 2734                              Success(containing_module) => {
 2735                                  search_module = containing_module;
 2736                                  start_index = 1;
 2737                              }
 2738                          }
 2739                      }
 2740                  }
 2741              }
 2742              Success(PrefixFound(containing_module, index)) => {
 2743                  search_module = containing_module;
 2744                  start_index = index;
 2745              }
 2746          }
 2747  
 2748          self.resolve_module_path_from_root(search_module,
 2749                                             module_path,
 2750                                             start_index,
 2751                                             span,
 2752                                             name_search_type)
 2753      }
 2754  
 2755      /// Invariant: This must only be called during main resolution, not during
 2756      /// import resolution.
 2757      pub fn resolve_item_in_lexical_scope(@mut self,
 2758                                           module_: @mut Module,
 2759                                           name: ident,
 2760                                           namespace: Namespace,
 2761                                           search_through_modules:
 2762                                           SearchThroughModulesFlag)
 2763                                           -> ResolveResult<Target> {
 2764          debug!("(resolving item in lexical scope) resolving `%s` in \
 2765                  namespace %? in `%s`",
 2766                 self.session.str_of(name),
 2767                 namespace,
 2768                 self.module_to_str(module_));
 2769  
 2770          // The current module node is handled specially. First, check for
 2771          // its immediate children.
 2772          match module_.children.find(&name) {
 2773              Some(name_bindings)
 2774                      if name_bindings.defined_in_namespace(namespace) => {
 2775                  return Success(Target(module_, *name_bindings));
 2776              }
 2777              Some(_) | None => { /* Not found; continue. */ }
 2778          }
 2779  
 2780          // Now check for its import directives. We don't have to have resolved
 2781          // all its imports in the usual way; this is because chains of
 2782          // adjacent import statements are processed as though they mutated the
 2783          // current scope.
 2784          match module_.import_resolutions.find(&name) {
 2785              None => {
 2786                  // Not found; continue.
 2787              }
 2788              Some(import_resolution) => {
 2789                  match (*import_resolution).target_for_namespace(namespace) {
 2790                      None => {
 2791                          // Not found; continue.

 2846                                      search_module = parent_module_node;
 2847                                  }
 2848                              }
 2849                          }
 2850                          SearchThroughModules => {
 2851                              search_module = parent_module_node;
 2852                          }
 2853                      }
 2854                  }

 2970      /// Resolves a "module prefix". A module prefix is one of (a) `self::`;
 2971      /// (b) some chain of `super::`.

 2974                                   module_path: &[ident])
 2975                                   -> ResolveResult<ModulePrefixResult> {

 2977          // top of the crate otherwise.

 2998                  None => return Failed,
 2999                  Some(new_module) => {
 3000                      containing_module = new_module;
 3001                      i += 1;
 3002                  }
 3003              }
 3004          }
 3005  
 3006          debug!("(resolving module prefix) finished resolving prefix at %s",
 3007                 self.module_to_str(containing_module));

 3009          return Success(PrefixFound(containing_module, i));

 3251                                                           true)
 3252                      }
 3253                      _ => ()
 3254                  }
 3255              }
 3256          }
 3257      }
 3258  
 3259      // AST resolution
 3260      //
 3261      // We maintain a list of value ribs and type ribs.
 3262      //
 3263      // Simultaneously, we keep track of the current position in the module
 3264      // graph in the `current_module` pointer. When we go to resolve a name in
 3265      // the value or type namespaces, we first look through all the ribs and
 3266      // then query the module graph. When we resolve a name in the module
 3267      // namespace, we can skip all the ribs (since nested modules are not
 3268      // allowed within blocks in Rust) and jump straight to the current module
 3269      // graph node.
 3270      //
 3271      // Named implementations are handled separately. When we find a method
 3272      // call, we consult the module node to find all of the implementations in
 3273      // scope. This information is lazily cached in the module node. We then
 3274      // generate a fake "implementation scope" containing all the
 3275      // implementations thus found, for compatibility with old resolve pass.
 3276  
 3277      pub fn with_scope(@mut self, name: Option<ident>, f: &fn()) {
 3278          let orig_module = self.current_module;
 3279  
 3280          // Move down in the graph.
 3281          match name {
 3282              None => {
 3283                  // Nothing to do.
 3284              }
 3285              Some(name) => {
 3286                  match orig_module.children.find(&name) {
 3287                      None => {
 3288                          debug!("!!! (with scope) didn't find `%s` in `%s`",
 3289                                 self.session.str_of(name),
 3290                                 self.module_to_str(orig_module));
 3291                      }
 3292                      Some(name_bindings) => {
 3293                          match (*name_bindings).get_module_if_available() {
 3294                              None => {
 3295                                  debug!("!!! (with scope) didn't find module \
 3296                                          for `%s` in `%s`",
 3297                                         self.session.str_of(name),
 3298                                         self.module_to_str(orig_module));
 3299                              }
 3300                              Some(module_) => {
 3301                                  self.current_module = module_;
 3302                              }
 3303                          }
 3304                      }
 3305                  }
 3306              }
 3307          }
 3308  
 3309          f();
 3310  
 3311          self.current_module = orig_module;
 3312      }

 3314      /// Wraps the given definition in the appropriate number of `def_upvar`
 3315      /// wrappers.
 3316      pub fn upvarify(@mut self,
 3317                      ribs: &mut ~[@Rib],
 3318                      rib_index: uint,
 3319                      def_like: def_like,
 3320                      span: span,
 3321                      allow_capturing_self: AllowCapturingSelfFlag)
 3322                      -> Option<def_like> {
 3323          let mut def;
 3324          let is_ty_param;
 3325  
 3326          match def_like {
 3327              dl_def(d @ def_local(*)) | dl_def(d @ def_upvar(*)) |
 3328              dl_def(d @ def_arg(*)) | dl_def(d @ def_binding(*)) => {
 3329                  def = d;
 3330                  is_ty_param = false;
 3331              }
 3332              dl_def(d @ def_ty_param(*)) => {
 3333                  def = d;
 3334                  is_ty_param = true;
 3335              }
 3336              dl_def(d @ def_self(*))
 3337                      if allow_capturing_self == DontAllowCapturingSelf => {
 3338                  def = d;
 3339                  is_ty_param = false;
 3340              }
 3341              _ => {
 3342                  return Some(def_like);
 3343              }
 3344          }
 3345  
 3346          let mut rib_index = rib_index + 1;
 3347          while rib_index < ribs.len() {
 3348              match ribs[rib_index].kind {
 3349                  NormalRibKind => {
 3350                      // Nothing to do. Continue.
 3351                  }
 3352                  FunctionRibKind(function_id, body_id) => {
 3353                      if !is_ty_param {
 3354                          def = def_upvar(def_id_of_def(def).node,
 3355                                          @def,
 3356                                          function_id,
 3357                                          body_id);
 3358                      }
 3359                  }
 3360                  MethodRibKind(item_id, _) => {
 3361                    // If the def is a ty param, and came from the parent
 3362                    // item, it's ok
 3363                    match def {
 3364                      def_ty_param(did, _)
 3365                          if self.def_map.find(&did.node).map_move(|x| *x)
 3366                              == Some(def_typaram_binder(item_id)) => {
 3367                        // ok
 3368                      }
 3369                      _ => {
 3370                      if !is_ty_param {
 3371                          // This was an attempt to access an upvar inside a
 3372                          // named function item. This is not allowed, so we
 3373                          // report an error.
 3374  
 3375                          self.session.span_err(
 3376                              span,
 3377                              "can't capture dynamic environment in a fn item; \
 3378                              use the || { ... } closure form instead");
 3379                      } else {
 3380                          // This was an attempt to use a type parameter outside
 3381                          // its scope.
 3382  
 3383                          self.session.span_err(span,
 3384                                                "attempt to use a type \
 3385                                                argument out of scope");
 3386                      }
 3387  
 3388                      return None;
 3389                      }
 3390                    }
 3391                  }
 3392                  OpaqueFunctionRibKind => {
 3393                      if !is_ty_param {
 3394                          // This was an attempt to access an upvar inside a
 3395                          // named function item. This is not allowed, so we
 3396                          // report an error.
 3397  
 3398                          self.session.span_err(
 3399                              span,
 3400                              "can't capture dynamic environment in a fn item; \
 3401                              use the || { ... } closure form instead");
 3402                      } else {
 3403                          // This was an attempt to use a type parameter outside
 3404                          // its scope.
 3405  
 3406                          self.session.span_err(span,
 3407                                                "attempt to use a type \
 3408                                                argument out of scope");
 3409                      }
 3410  
 3411                      return None;
 3412                  }
 3413                  ConstantItemRibKind => {
 3414                      // Still doesn't deal with upvars
 3415                      self.session.span_err(span,
 3416                                            "attempt to use a non-constant \
 3417                                             value in a constant");
 3418  
 3419                  }
 3420              }
 3421  
 3422              rib_index += 1;
 3423          }
 3424  
 3425          return Some(dl_def(def));
 3426      }

 3428      pub fn search_ribs(@mut self,
 3429                         ribs: &mut ~[@Rib],
 3430                         name: ident,
 3431                         span: span,
 3432                         allow_capturing_self: AllowCapturingSelfFlag)
 3433                         -> Option<def_like> {
 3434          // FIXME #4950: This should not use a while loop.
 3435          // FIXME #4950: Try caching?
 3436  
 3437          let mut i = ribs.len();
 3438          while i != 0 {
 3439              i -= 1;
 3440              match ribs[i].bindings.find(&name) {
 3441                  Some(&def_like) => {
 3442                      return self.upvarify(ribs, i, def_like, span,
 3443                                           allow_capturing_self);
 3444                  }
 3445                  None => {
 3446                      // Continue.
 3447                  }
 3448              }
 3449          }
 3450  
 3451          return None;
 3452      }

 3474      pub fn resolve_item(@mut self, item: @item, visitor: ResolveVisitor) {

 3477  
 3478          // Items with the !resolve_unexported attribute are X-ray contexts.

 3655      pub fn with_type_parameter_rib(@mut self,
 3656                                     type_parameters: TypeParameters,
 3657                                     f: &fn()) {

 3659              HasTypeParameters(generics, node_id, initial_index,
 3660                                rib_kind) => {

 3666                      let name = type_parameter.ident;

 3668                             type_parameter.id);

 3670                          (local_def(type_parameter.id),
 3671                           index + initial_index));
 3672                      // Associate this type parameter with
 3673                      // the item that bound it
 3674                      self.record_def(type_parameter.id,
 3675                                      def_typaram_binder(node_id));

 3677                  }
 3678              }
 3679  
 3680              NoTypeParameters => {
 3681                  // Nothing to do.
 3682              }
 3683          }
 3684  
 3685          f();
 3686  
 3687          match type_parameters {
 3688              HasTypeParameters(*) => {
 3689                  self.type_ribs.pop();

 3691  
 3692              NoTypeParameters => {
 3693                  // Nothing to do.

 3710      pub fn resolve_function(@mut self,
 3711                              rib_kind: RibKind,
 3712                              optional_declaration: Option<&fn_decl>,
 3713                              type_parameters: TypeParameters,
 3714                              block: &Block,
 3715                              self_binding: SelfBinding,
 3716                              visitor: ResolveVisitor) {
 3717          // Create a value rib for the function.
 3718          let function_value_rib = @Rib(rib_kind);
 3719          self.value_ribs.push(function_value_rib);
 3720  
 3721          // Create a label rib for the function.
 3722          let function_label_rib = @Rib(rib_kind);
 3723          self.label_ribs.push(function_label_rib);
 3724  
 3725          // If this function has type parameters, add them now.
 3726          do self.with_type_parameter_rib(type_parameters) {
 3727              // Resolve the type parameters.

 3761                                               binding_mode,
 3762                                               mutability,

 3764                                               visitor);

 4020      pub fn check_consistent_bindings(@mut self, arm: &arm) {
 4021          if arm.pats.len() == 0 { return; }
 4022          let map_0 = self.binding_mode_map(arm.pats[0]);
 4023          for (i, p) in arm.pats.iter().enumerate() {
 4024              let map_i = self.binding_mode_map(*p);
 4025  
 4026              for (&key, &binding_0) in map_0.iter() {
 4027                  match map_i.find(&key) {
 4028                    None => {
 4029                      self.session.span_err(
 4030                          p.span,
 4031                          fmt!("variable `%s` from pattern #1 is \
 4032                                    not bound in pattern #%u",
 4033                               self.session.str_of(key), i + 1));
 4034                    }
 4035                    Some(binding_i) => {
 4036                      if binding_0.binding_mode != binding_i.binding_mode {
 4037                          self.session.span_err(
 4038                              binding_i.span,
 4039                              fmt!("variable `%s` is bound with different \
 4040                                        mode in pattern #%u than in pattern #1",
 4041                                   self.session.str_of(key), i + 1));
 4042                      }
 4043                    }
 4044                  }
 4045              }
 4046  
 4047              for (&key, &binding) in map_i.iter() {
 4048                  if !map_0.contains_key(&key) {
 4049                      self.session.span_err(
 4050                          binding.span,
 4051                          fmt!("variable `%s` from pattern #%u is \
 4052                                    not bound in pattern #1",
 4053                               self.session.str_of(key), i + 1));
 4054                  }
 4055              }
 4056          }
 4057      }

 4091          }
 4092  
 4093          // Descend into the block.
 4094          visit_block(block, ((), visitor));

 4097          self.current_module = orig_module;

 4211                      // such a value is simply disallowed (since it's rarely
 4212                      // what you want).
 4213

 4224                                  pattern,
 4225                                  binding_mode,

 4263                                      // `def_binding` definitions.

 4282

 4284                              // doesn't already exist in the bindings list. (We
 4285                              // must not add it if it's in the bindings list

 4475      pub fn resolve_path(@mut self,
 4476                          id: NodeId,
 4477                          path: &Path,
 4478                          namespace: Namespace,

 4494              *path.idents.last(), namespace, check_ribs, path.span);

 4500                  (Some(d), Some(ud)) if d == ud => {

 4502                                            id, path.span,

 4505                  _ => ()

 4508          }

 4511      }

 4536      // FIXME #4952: Merge me with resolve_name_in_module?

 4832      pub fn find_best_match_for_name(@mut self,
 4833                                      name: &str,
 4834                                      max_distance: uint)
 4835                                      -> Option<@str> {
 4836          let this = &mut *self;
 4837  
 4838          let mut maybes: ~[@str] = ~[];
 4839          let mut values: ~[uint] = ~[];
 4840  
 4841          let mut j = this.value_ribs.len();
 4842          while j != 0 {
 4843              j -= 1;
 4844              for (&k, _) in this.value_ribs[j].bindings.iter() {
 4845                  maybes.push(this.session.str_of(k));
 4846                  values.push(uint::max_value);
 4847              }
 4848          }
 4849  
 4850          let mut smallest = 0;
 4851          for (i, &other) in maybes.iter().enumerate() {
 4852              values[i] = name.lev_distance(other);
 4853  
 4854              if values[i] <= values[smallest] {
 4855                  smallest = i;
 4856              }
 4857          }
 4858  
 4859          if values.len() > 0 &&
 4860              values[smallest] != uint::max_value &&
 4861              values[smallest] < name.len() + 2 &&
 4862              values[smallest] <= max_distance &&
 4863              name != maybes[smallest] {
 4864  
 4865              Some(maybes.swap_remove(smallest))
 4866  
 4867          } else {
 4868              None
 4869          }
 4870      }

 4891                                }
 4892                              }
 4893                          }

 4897                    }
